I"Ã<p>Silly name for a delicious dish I invented:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Slice three or four leeks in 1cm- disks</li>
  <li>Arrange flat on baking sheet</li>
  <li>Add olive oil, little salt and pepper</li>
  <li>Put in oven at 200 for 10-15 minutes (until they start to brown)</li>
  <li>Turn oven down to 150</li>
  <li>Ladle with brine made of white wine, pomegranate molasse</li>
  <li>Continue until brown and delicious</li>
  <li>May take hours</li>
</ul>
